    "Moreover, the possibility of having lepton flavour violation implies that modes such as those induced by b → sℓ - 1 ℓ + 2 with ℓ 1 ̸ = ℓ 2, can occur and are correlated both to purely leptonic LFV processes, µ -→ e -γ, τ -→ µ -µ + µ -, µ -→ e -e + e -and µ -→ e -conversion in nuclei, as well as to the LFC b → sℓ -ℓ + transitions.",
    "To summarize our main findings, we remark that:• Imposing ∆F = 2 constraints, the NP contributions to the Wilson coefficients Re(C NP 9) ℓℓ and Re(C NP 10) ℓℓ, ℓ = µ, τ, are found to be at the ≃ 10% level of the corresponding SM coefficients.",
